Reben's Luncheonette is the tiny hole in the wall between McDonalds and Chase bank. It has survived the Williamsburg gentrification phase thus far, which is great!  The place is full at all times of the day. That is the clear indication of good food. Reben's is a great cheap spot to grab a quick breakfast. It sits about ten people max; this is not an ideal place to dine, though. So your options are to place your order to go or chow down your food fast.  These guys make THE best home fries. They are consistent with it too. It is never burnt or clumped up as I have experienced at other places. Solid scrambled eggs with cheese on top. If you have never had the pleasure of drinking a morir sonando drop everything you are doing and make your way to Reben's asap (forgetaboutit if your lactose intolerant). Morir sonando (die dreaming) is the delicious concoction that Dominicans thought up. It is freshly squeezed orange juice mixed with milk and sugar. Don't knock it until you try it!  Don't worry about smelling like food after eating at Reben's because you won't. I am not the type of girl that is ok with eating at places where the smells of the food will stick to my clothes. So worry not, even though it is a tight spot.  The guys that run Reben's are always happy, courteous, and fast. I highly recommend this place if you are in the area and want a quick bite.

The reason I give a 5 star was because of everything worked out perfectly. My original plans was going to streets restaurant...but they are closed permanently.  Walked Into Ruben and it was like walking in to your favorite uncle or cousins house. Your basic breakfast place which is fast..in 5 mins u hve breakfast fully cooked in front of me. The cook was so friendly and nice. It felt like long lost family. Had 2 fried eggs, home fries and grilled salami. Omg, reminded me of growing up. Now not the healthiest choices with the salami but it was straight and to the point with friendly atmosphere. Apparently the mornings are full with people. Luckily was there at 2pm. Also had a morrir sonando drink that was prepared fresh and good. Sweet oranges with milk. There was enough for 2 people. I left so stuffed and it was so cheap. It's a nice place for a quick bite that's just refreshingly simple and good.

Who would have thought that orange juice and milk combined would be a good thing?  My entire life I had the notion that oranges and milk should never cross paths. I don't know where it came from, it was just one of those weird things that get inside a person's head and becomes part of their belief system. Now, as an adult I know that I was wrong. And why? Two words: morir soñando.  Orange juice, evaporated milk, sugar and crushed ice vigorously stirred to a smooth, frothy consistency this gift from the Dominican Republic is the stuff of dreams.  Unfortunately I cannot tell you any more about the menu at Reuben Luncheonette as I've only ever ordered this one thing. The staff are always friendly and seem somewhat amused by our single mindedness when we visit.  If you only want to try a taste of morir soñando and aren't ready for a full one, there are often leftovers that are put out as samples so keep your eyes peeled when you are there.
